               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">loss of output voltage</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid id="WhenTheManualBypassSwitchIsInBypass-5745E8F4"
                           class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When
the manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position, it is not possible
for the system to automatically switch back to inverter operation
in case the bypass mains becomes unavailable.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">With a manual bypass switch it
is possible to manually switch and lock the system in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position to isolate sections.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The system has an external manual
bypass switch that helps to isolate the system in manual bypass.</p>
         <note class="- topic/note ">This mode is also called manual bypass because the load is
supplied over the manual bypass switch.</note>
